ce:section.ce:para:
The Fe3O4@CS@GO magnetic nanocomposite was prepared according to the previous literature with slight modification. Firstly, 0.05 g of graphene oxide (GO) was added into 25 mL of ultrapure water and dispersed under ultrasonic for 120 min. The Fe3O4@CS magnetic nanoparticles were mixed with above GO suspension under continuous ultrasonic for 60 min. Subsequently, 1.25 mL of epichlorohydrin was added dropwise into the mixed solution and reacted under stirring at 50 °C for 1 h. After completing this reaction, sodium hydroxide solution was added dropwise to adjust the pH value of the above solution to 11 and then the obtained solution was stirred for 4 h. Finally, the magnetic nanocomposite was separated by a magnet and washed repeatedly with ultrapure water until the supernatant became neutral. Additionally, the dark brown magnetic nanocomposite of Fe3O
                           4
                        @CS@GO was obtained by drying the solid product under vacuum at 60 °C.
